C) legally','(D) legalizes','The governmental department used to provide financial aid, but now it offers _____ services only.',NULL,5),(23,'B','explanation',3,'(A) expressive','(B) reliable','(C) partial','(D) extreme','Mr. Sims needs a more _____ vehicle for commuting from his suburban home to his office downtown.',NULL,5),(24,'B','explanation',4,'(A) experience','(B) growth','(C) formula','(D) incentive','The contractor had a fifteen-percent _____ in his business after advertising in the local newspaper.',NULL,5),(25,'D','explanation',5,'(A) accessorized','(B) accessorize','(C) accessorizes','(D) accessories','The upscale boutique Jane’s Closet is known for selling the most stylish _____ for young professionals.',NULL,5),(26,'A','explanation',1,'(A) soon','(B) very','(C) that','(D) still','The store’s manager plans to put the new merchandise on display _____ to promote the line of fall fashions.',NULL,6),(27,'D','explanation',2,'(A) proceeds','(B) perspectives','(C) installments','(D) stages','The riskiest _____ of the development of new medications are the trials with human subjects.',NULL,6),(28,'C','explanation',3,'(A) quote','(B) graduation','(C) request','(D) dispute','At the guest’s _____ , an extra set of towels and complimentary soaps were brought to the room.',NULL,6),(29,'B','explanation',4,'(A) yet','(B) just','(C) few','(D) still','The building owner purchased the property _____ three months ago, but she has already spent a great deal of money on renovations.',NULL,6),(30,'B','explanation',5,'(A) fix','(B) write','(C) send','(D) direct','When filling out the order form, please _____ your address clearly to prevent delays.',NULL,6);
